The paper deals with matrix completion problems, which are often studied in the sub-fields of computer science related to data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). The problem of Closest String with Wildcards, which is a part of the paper's research, is a stringology problem and can be categorized under computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms and data structures for strings (cs.DS). The paper also discusses parameterized complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
